data.title: eyemartexpress.com @ PissedConsumer
data.meta_description: Eyemart Express has 44 reviews (average rating 2.2). Consumers say: Still waiting on glasses I paid for in 7/1/24, Poor service
data.text:
Shelley in the Florence SC store was rude. She cut off my sister three times from asking questions.

She told my sister that if she would be quiet, then she could correct what she was saying to her.

At no time should she have spoken to the customer in this manner. The customer is spending good money and has a right to ask questions.

The guy didn't help me. He gave me glasses but never checked if they needed adjustment.

He argued with me. I wanted a refund, but was told only the manager could authorize it, who wasn't working at the time.

Now, I am being offered an adjustment by Manny. However, it's not much of an offer since that is supposed to be their obligation.

On April 19 at approximately 1:55 pm, After 30 min I told clerks I was only doing a pickup. I was told to seat and wait until my name was called behind all the people that were making selections and filling prescriptions, etc.

When I told that Black heavy set female with long hair, that it would only take a few minutes and I could be gone. She started mouthing that I was another one of thoses customer that didnt know how to follow orders and I need to sit down because store policy required I wait until my name is called. When I suggested 2 lines/list, one for pickup only and one for people with prescription, she rudely said you to sit down or you come back later. I asked just for a 5 min.

pickup. She got ruder. Thats when I asked for the headquarters number to file a complaint. Jada (Nada?) waited on me about 20 minutes later.

It took less than 3 minutes for me to get my pickup. I waited at 30-40 minutes for a 3 minute pickup. I made the same suggestions to Jada(Nada?). She said we are short staff the customer has to accept that.

That's the best they could.

By the way, several customers were dissatisfied at the wait time just pickup glasses. One or two others voiced their complaint but must didnt.

When I booked my appointment over the phone I was asked "if I had insurance?" I reply yes and told her the insurance I had...she replied "perfect" and continued to set up my appointment. I arrived at my scheduled appointment, proceeded with my eye exam.

Once finished I was told that my bill would be $90...WAIT, my insurance covers free eye exams. Apparently, Eyemart Express DIDN'T accept my insurance and stated to me that I was out of network. I paid the $90 and walked out of Eyemart Express feeling SCAMMED, mislead and very angry.

So thank you Eyemart Express for ripping me off. I will not return and will definitely post on social media.

Eyemart Express de Zavala IH10 , San Antonio, TX 78230 . Worst people ever seen.

My lenses were faded just after 3 months. And they wont fix it. Some unprofessional girl name page talked to me over the phone and wouldnt even give me her last name. She is so unprofessional and scared to give her name.

Said that my manager is on vacation and nobody else has the authority to make a decision. So I have to wait until the manager comes back from vacation. Sounds like a small convenient store in a third world country where if the owner is not there, nobody can take care of customers.

Shut down your convenient store if your owner is on vacation. Stop stealing customers money.
